The paper deals with the construction of a spanner in the LOCAL model, which is a distributed computing model. Therefore, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category. The paper also involves graph theory and algorithms, which suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as another likely category. The use of unique edge IDs and the analysis of message complexity indicate cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as a possible category. The paper also involves information theory, which suggests cs.IT (Information Theory) as a possible category. Finally, the paper deals with the improvement of message complexity in distributed algorithms, which suggests cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as a possible category.
